title.@value: Fetus or newborn affected by caesarean delivery

definition.@value: A condition characterised by findings in the fetus or newborn due to delivery via a surgical procedure in which one or more incisions are made through a mother's abdomen (laparotomy) and uterus (hysterotomy) to deliver one or more babies (Caesarean delivery).

label.@value: Fetus or newborn affected by caesarean delivery
fetus or neonate affected by caesarean section
